<paper id="1843547622"><title>Building Compact Competent Case-Bases</title><year>1999</year><authors><author org="university College Dublin" id="2133336528">Barry Smyth</author><author org="university College Dublin" id="2163263079">Elizabeth McKenna</author></authors><n_citation>106</n_citation><doc_type>Conference</doc_type><references><reference>36794914</reference><reference>1480107956</reference><reference>1483055888</reference><reference>1536612688</reference><reference>1562059814</reference><reference>1980452149</reference><reference>1989333493</reference><reference>1994410331</reference><reference>2019762723</reference><reference>2034324715</reference><reference>2053591567</reference><reference>2088777431</reference><reference>2098631313</reference><reference>2107686700</reference><reference>2115563868</reference><reference>2122496402</reference><reference>2136333413</reference><reference>2147169507</reference></references><venue id="1168666102" type="C">International Conference on Case-Based Reasoning</venue><doi>10.1007/3-540-48508-2_24</doi><keywords><keyword weight="0.47591">Computer science</keyword><keyword weight="0.42739">Reuse</keyword><keyword weight="0.0">Competence model</keyword><keyword weight="0.0">Learning by example</keyword><keyword weight="0.47839">Artificial intelligence</keyword><keyword weight="0.61782">Case-based reasoning</keyword><keyword weight="0.47279">Machine learning</keyword></keywords><publisher>Springer, Berlin, Heidelberg</publisher><abstract>Case-based reasoning systems solve problems by reusing a corpus of previous problem solving experience stored as a case-base of individual problem solving cases. In this paper we describe a new technique for constructing compact competent case-bases. The technique is novel in its use of an explicit model of case competence. This allows cases to be selected on the basis of their individual competence contributions. An experimental study shows how this technique compares favorably to more traditional strategies across a range of standard data-sets.</abstract></paper>